# Test AIF Definition

> Include: ../catala/aifmd_article_4.catala_en

Covers AIFDefinition (Article 4(1)(a)) including each negating
criterion, and AIFExclusions (Article 2) including the holding-company
condition and the base/final relationship.

## Shared fund profiles

```catala-metadata
declaration standard_aif content FundCharacteristics equals
  FundCharacteristics {
    -- is_collective_investment_undertaking: true
    -- raises_capital_from_investors: true
    -- number_of_investors: 10
    -- has_defined_investment_policy: true
    -- invests_for_investor_benefit: true
    -- requires_ucits_authorization: false
  }

declaration no_exclusion content ExclusionCheck equals
  ExclusionCheck {
    -- exclusion_category: NoExclusion
    -- is_holding_company_per_article_4: false
  }
```

## Article 4(1)(a) — AIFDefinition

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope Test_StandardAIF:
  output status content AIFDefinition

scope Test_StandardAIF:
  definition status equals output of AIFDefinition with
    { -- fund: standard_aif }
  assertion status.qualifies_as_aif

#[test]
declaration scope Test_SingleInvestor_NotAIF:
  output status content AIFDefinition

scope Test_SingleInvestor_NotAIF:
  # "a number of investors" encoded as >= 2; one investor fails.
  definition status equals output of AIFDefinition with
    { -- fund: FundCharacteristics {
        -- is_collective_investment_undertaking: true
        -- raises_capital_from_investors: true
        -- number_of_investors: 1
        -- has_defined_investment_policy: true
        -- invests_for_investor_benefit: true
        -- requires_ucits_authorization: false
      } }
  assertion not status.qualifies_as_aif

#[test]
declaration scope Test_UCITS_NotAIF:
  output status content AIFDefinition

scope Test_UCITS_NotAIF:
  definition status equals output of AIFDefinition with
    { -- fund: FundCharacteristics {
        -- is_collective_investment_undertaking: true
        -- raises_capital_from_investors: true
        -- number_of_investors: 10
        -- has_defined_investment_policy: true
        -- invests_for_investor_benefit: true
        -- requires_ucits_authorization: true
      } }
  assertion not status.qualifies_as_aif

#[test]
declaration scope Test_NoInvestorBenefit_NotAIF:
  output status content AIFDefinition

scope Test_NoInvestorBenefit_NotAIF:
  # The criterion the drifted AIFExclusions restatement used to omit.
  definition status equals output of AIFDefinition with
    { -- fund: FundCharacteristics {
        -- is_collective_investment_undertaking: true
        -- raises_capital_from_investors: true
        -- number_of_investors: 10
        -- has_defined_investment_policy: true
        -- invests_for_investor_benefit: false
        -- requires_ucits_authorization: false
      } }
  assertion not status.qualifies_as_aif
```

## Article 2 — AIFExclusions

```catala
#[test]
declaration scope Test_NoExclusion_FinalEqualsBase:
  output status content AIFExclusions

scope Test_NoExclusion_FinalEqualsBase:
  definition status equals output of AIFExclusions with
    { -- fund: standard_aif
      -- exclusions: no_exclusion }
  assertion status.base_aif_status
  assertion not status.is_excluded
  assertion status.final_aif_status

#[test]
declaration scope Test_BaseTracksDefinition:
  output status content AIFExclusions

scope Test_BaseTracksDefinition:
  # base_aif_status delegates to AIFDefinition: a fund failing the
  # investor-benefit criterion is not a base AIF here either.
  definition status equals output of AIFExclusions with
    { -- fund: FundCharacteristics {
        -- is_collective_investment_undertaking: true
        -- raises_capital_from_investors: true
        -- number_of_investors: 10
        -- has_defined_investment_policy: true
        -- invests_for_investor_benefit: false
        -- requires_ucits_authorization: false
      }
      -- exclusions: no_exclusion }
  assertion not status.base_aif_status
  assertion not status.final_aif_status

#[test]
declaration scope Test_PensionFund_Excluded:
  output status content AIFExclusions

scope Test_PensionFund_Excluded:
  definition status equals output of AIFExclusions with
    { -- fund: standard_aif
      -- exclusions: ExclusionCheck {
           -- exclusion_category: PensionFund
           -- is_holding_company_per_article_4: false
         } }
  assertion status.base_aif_status
  assertion status.is_excluded
  assertion not status.final_aif_status

#[test]
declaration scope Test_HoldingCompany_PerArticle4_Excluded:
  output status content AIFExclusions

scope Test_HoldingCompany_PerArticle4_Excluded:
  definition status equals output of AIFExclusions with
    { -- fund: standard_aif
      -- exclusions: ExclusionCheck {
           -- exclusion_category: HoldingCompany
           -- is_holding_company_per_article_4: true
         } }
  assertion status.is_excluded
  assertion not status.final_aif_status

#[test]
declaration scope Test_HoldingCompany_NotPerArticle4_NotExcluded:
  output status content AIFExclusions

scope Test_HoldingCompany_NotPerArticle4_NotExcluded:
  # The holding-company exclusion is conditional on the Article 4
  # holding-company definition being met, unlike the categorical
  # exclusions.
  definition status equals output of AIFExclusions with
    { -- fund: standard_aif
      -- exclusions: ExclusionCheck {
           -- exclusion_category: HoldingCompany
           -- is_holding_company_per_article_4: false
         } }
  assertion not status.is_excluded
  assertion status.final_aif_status

#[test]
declaration scope Test_CentralBank_Excluded:
  output status content AIFExclusions

scope Test_CentralBank_Excluded:
  definition status equals output of AIFExclusions with
    { -- fund: standard_aif
      -- exclusions: ExclusionCheck {
           -- exclusion_category: CentralBank
           -- is_holding_company_per_article_4: false
         } }
  assertion status.is_excluded
  assertion not status.final_aif_status
```
